# Rename completed plans in-place without committing

## Overview

Replace the current "move plan to `completed/` subdirectory + git commit" behavior with an in-place rename that appends `-completed` to the plan filename (preserving extension) and does **not** create a git commit. This matches the common case where the plan file is gitignored and shouldn't be tracked.

Example renames:
- `tasks/0009-no-commit/preprompt` â†’ `tasks/0009-no-commit/preprompt-completed`
- `docs/plans/2026-04-30-feature.md` â†’ `docs/plans/2026-04-30-feature-completed.md`

